00:05:55.024 --> 00:05:58.166
So Williams syndrome is pretty specific

00:05:58.166 --> 00:06:01.339
and does depend at least these days

00:06:01.339 --> 00:06:03.956
on the genetic underpinnings.

00:06:03.956 --> 00:06:08.123
I will mention, this is a
little bit of a tangent, but

00:06:09.109 --> 00:06:11.153
in my slide I didn't emphasize this,

00:06:11.153 --> 00:06:15.762
but 96, more than 96%
of people with autism

00:06:15.762 --> 00:06:17.512
have almost the exact

00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:22.254
same deletion on chromosome seven,

00:06:23.568 --> 00:06:26.731
and this is highly unusual
that it's so stereotyped,

00:06:26.731 --> 00:06:30.547
and this is because of what I explained,

00:06:30.547 --> 00:06:34.714
their flanking regions having
very similar sequences of DNA

00:06:36.098 --> 00:06:38.776
and sort of getting mixed up.

00:06:38.776 --> 00:06:42.865
However, there are very
rare people who have

00:06:42.865 --> 00:06:47.032
smaller deletions in that same
portion of chromosome seven,

00:06:48.460 --> 00:06:52.627
and they have only pieces
of the Williams syndrome

00:06:53.897 --> 00:06:55.922
clinical phenotype.

00:06:55.922 --> 00:07:00.089
For example, people who just
have a couple of genes deleted

00:07:01.037 --> 00:07:05.837
called elastin and LEMK1
have the spatial problems

00:07:05.837 --> 00:07:08.237
but not the personality problems.

00:07:08.237 --> 00:07:11.959
So these very rare folks, and
we've now brought to the NIH

00:07:11.959 --> 00:07:15.209
for study five families, five kindreds,

00:07:16.260 --> 00:07:20.427
and seven singleton children
who have these small deletions,

00:07:21.521 --> 00:07:24.694
and we hope that that will enable us

00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:28.527
to sort of dissect the
genes that are involved

00:07:29.443 --> 00:07:32.111
in a more specific way.

00:07:32.111 --> 00:07:34.875
My point in bringing this
up is that the people

00:07:34.875 --> 00:07:37.621
who have these just several genes deleted,

00:07:37.621 --> 00:07:42.147
are not picked up because they
have the behavioral phenotype

00:07:42.147 --> 00:07:44.148
at all, they're actually picked up

00:07:44.148 --> 00:07:46.595
because they have a cardiac problem.

00:07:46.595 --> 00:07:49.892
Because one of the gene's
that's hemideleted is elastin,

00:07:49.892 --> 00:07:52.858
which forms the walls of our arteries.

00:07:52.858 --> 00:07:56.595
So they have a cardiovascular problem

00:07:56.595 --> 00:07:57.810
and they're picked up.

00:07:57.810 --> 00:08:00.462
And it's only apparent that
they have the visuo-spatial

00:08:00.462 --> 00:08:04.098
construct problem when they're tested.

00:08:04.098 --> 00:08:05.891
But they'll tell you if you talk to them,

00:08:05.891 --> 00:08:08.216
you know, gee I had problems in this area

00:08:08.216 --> 00:08:11.517
in school, I wasn't very good in geometry,

00:08:11.517 --> 00:08:14.188
and in other things like that.

00:08:14.188 --> 00:08:16.436
So, the short answer is no.

00:08:16.436 --> 00:08:18.227
I don't think that we pick up people

00:08:18.227 --> 00:08:21.083
who have idiopathic Williams syndrome

00:08:21.083 --> 00:08:24.405
because it is by definition
a genetic disorder

00:08:24.405 --> 00:08:25.733
now that we know about it,

00:08:25.733 --> 00:08:28.304
