00:09:10.157 --> 00:09:14.400
But people have been
able to use viruses to

00:09:14.400 --> 00:09:18.939
manipulate the levels of FOXP2
protein that the gene makes

00:09:18.939 --> 00:09:21.416
in certain parts of the brain.

00:09:21.416 --> 00:09:23.523
And people have studied

00:09:23.523 --> 00:09:27.409
one particular songbird
which is the zebra finch.

00:09:27.409 --> 00:09:30.572
So male, young male zebra finches,

00:09:30.572 --> 00:09:34.907
they hear a song sung
by an adult male tutor

00:09:34.907 --> 00:09:39.074
and they learn to make a
pretty accurate copy of that.

00:09:40.770 --> 00:09:42.572
And they're not the
prettiest songs in the world,

00:09:42.572 --> 00:09:43.960
zebra finch songs,

00:09:43.960 --> 00:09:47.324
but they have a certain
level of complexity and

00:09:47.324 --> 00:09:50.476
different syllable types
and different structures.

00:09:50.476 --> 00:09:52.678
And the males sing to the females,

00:09:52.678 --> 00:09:54.049
and it's a learned thing.

00:09:54.049 --> 00:09:57.132
They have to be exposed to a template

00:09:58.589 --> 00:10:00.433
when they're young.

00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:02.527
And lots is known about the neurobiology

00:10:02.527 --> 00:10:06.694
of how the zebra finch males
are able to learn these songs.

00:10:07.731 --> 00:10:11.186
And they have particular
parts of the brain,

00:10:11.186 --> 00:10:14.722
particular kind of nuclei in the brain

00:10:14.722 --> 00:10:18.832
including one in the
striatum called Area X.

00:10:18.832 --> 00:10:21.409
That are important for
this learning process.

00:10:21.409 --> 00:10:24.307
And so some researchers in Berlin,

00:10:24.307 --> 00:10:27.604
led by Constance Shaff, noticed

00:10:27.604 --> 00:10:30.727
that the levels of FOXP2
protein that were being made

00:10:30.727 --> 00:10:34.840
in Area X were going up
around the developmental time

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:37.218
when the birds are learning their songs.

00:10:37.218 --> 00:10:41.328
So they interfered with
using these viruses

00:10:41.328 --> 00:10:45.481
they injected these viruses into Area X of

00:10:45.481 --> 00:10:46.314
young

00:10:48.290 --> 00:10:49.917
birds learning these songs

00:10:49.917 --> 00:10:52.676
and they knocked down the
amount of FOXP2 was being made

00:10:52.676 --> 00:10:55.691
and they found that the
songs were then not copied

00:10:55.691 --> 00:10:59.858
as accurately as the control
birds who had the gene

00:11:01.175 --> 00:11:03.236
knocked down in a different place

00:11:03.236 --> 00:11:06.903
or ones that had a kind
of dummy knock down.

00:11:07.752 --> 00:11:09.820
And there's lots more work
that's been done on that

00:11:09.820 --> 00:11:12.960
but it's interesting to see
that this is something that

00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:15.343
this kind of auditory
guided vocal learning,

00:11:15.343 --> 00:11:18.001
the need to listen to something and then

00:11:18.001 --> 00:11:20.683
and reproduce a copy of
it can be interfered with

00:11:20.683 --> 00:11:23.850
in a songbird with FOXP2 knocked down.

