00:29:29.034 --> 00:29:31.861
Do you want to add something?

00:29:31.861 --> 00:29:33.680
- Yeah there's interesting work by

00:29:33.680 --> 00:29:36.804
Colwyn Trevarthen on
communicative musicality.

00:29:36.804 --> 00:29:39.935
Which I think goes back to
the early bonding between

00:29:39.935 --> 00:29:43.256
caregiver and babies, it seems that

00:29:43.256 --> 00:29:46.059
being in synchrony with
little vocalizations

00:29:46.059 --> 00:29:47.764
that infants make very early on

00:29:47.764 --> 00:29:51.106
is a critical part of
that bonding process.

00:29:51.106 --> 00:29:52.848
And it seems to precede language as well.

00:29:52.848 --> 00:29:56.023
