00:30:22.170 --> 00:30:25.482
the first kind of disruption
in that seen in autism

00:30:25.482 --> 00:30:27.049
is this thing called joint attention

00:30:27.049 --> 00:30:30.438
that infants are developing and

00:30:30.438 --> 00:30:33.021
so it's almost paradoxical that

00:30:34.725 --> 00:30:37.138
kind of these, a lot of
these savant abilities,

00:30:37.138 --> 00:30:41.160
or autistic and even
non-verbal autistic children

00:30:41.160 --> 00:30:44.620
might have very substantial
musical abilities

00:30:44.620 --> 00:30:46.694
and in fact you can begin to teach people

00:30:46.694 --> 00:30:48.721
and people with, even acquired aphasias,

00:30:48.721 --> 00:30:51.683
can do quite well if you
begin to get them to sing,

00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:53.299
you know using their right hemisphere.

00:30:53.299 --> 00:30:56.453
So I wonder, you know,
if you could elaborate

00:30:56.453 --> 00:31:00.620
that connection a little bit
for the neurologist in me.

00:31:01.778 --> 00:31:04.101
- Yeah I've just written a paper on

00:31:04.101 --> 00:31:06.267
is there such a thing as musical empathy

00:31:06.267 --> 00:31:08.252
as opposed to cognitive empathy

00:31:08.252 --> 00:31:10.417
and emotional empathy in everyday life

00:31:10.417 --> 00:31:12.606
and I think there is and I think

00:31:12.606 --> 00:31:14.674
the autistic children I work with

00:31:14.674 --> 00:31:16.056
often have musical empathy,

00:31:16.056 --> 00:31:20.116
so we can interrelate
humor, have teasing, have

00:31:20.116 --> 00:31:21.667
sadness, have joy,

00:31:21.667 --> 00:31:23.826
and yet they can't
empathize in everyday life,

00:31:23.826 --> 00:31:27.072
so I think that specifically
in the context of music

00:31:27.072 --> 00:31:28.393
there is that bonding

00:31:28.393 --> 00:31:30.914
but it doesn't seem to
transfer very easily.

00:31:30.914 --> 00:31:31.942
I think that's probably--

00:31:31.942 --> 00:31:33.825
- You know it's really
fascinating because they do

00:31:33.825 --> 00:31:36.596
a lot of children would love to be hugged

00:31:36.596 --> 00:31:39.365
and show kind of some kind of

00:31:39.365 --> 00:31:41.546
you know those emotional relationships

00:31:41.546 --> 00:31:44.172
but without the norm,
you know, the typical,

00:31:44.172 --> 00:31:47.713
that's really, it's
interesting, thank you.

