So in Alzheimer's often
the anatomic lesion

00:34:46.026 --> 00:34:48.991
for losing the ability
to say the word frog

00:34:48.991 --> 00:34:52.108
is posterior temporal parietal.

00:34:52.108 --> 00:34:55.190
These patients are very different, so

00:34:55.190 --> 00:34:58.107
Alzheimer patient frog, yeah, frog.

00:34:59.294 --> 00:35:01.535
So it's on the tip of the tongue.

00:35:01.535 --> 00:35:03.750
And it's very late in the
process that they lose

00:35:03.750 --> 00:35:05.643
the concept for a frog.

00:35:05.643 --> 00:35:09.424
But when the degeneration is
left anterior temporal lobe,

00:35:09.424 --> 00:35:13.599
the loss of the concept
of frog, what a frog is.

00:35:13.599 --> 00:35:17.218
These are people if you
give them an IQ test,

00:35:17.218 --> 00:35:21.037
the thing that they do worse
