00:39:22.771 --> 00:39:24.570
And of course there's an
enormous amount of human

00:39:24.570 --> 00:39:27.109
individual variability,
and that's the point.

00:39:27.109 --> 00:39:30.501
Is that you can't apply means, averages,

00:39:30.501 --> 00:39:32.650
groups, to individuals.

00:39:32.650 --> 00:39:36.445
And that's where things kind of get off.

00:39:36.445 --> 00:39:38.068
I'll just leave it there.

00:39:38.068 --> 00:39:40.777
I mean that's, I think
it's a very good point,

00:39:40.777 --> 00:39:43.172
and I think it gets
confounded, those two things.

00:39:43.172 --> 00:39:45.731
When somebody is speaking
about individual differences,

00:39:45.731 --> 00:39:48.015
they're not speaking about the average,

00:39:48.015 --> 00:39:49.729
they're speaking about individuals,

00:39:49.729 --> 00:39:52.337
and when you apply an
average to an individual

00:39:52.337 --> 00:39:55.339
you're losing a lot, usually wrong.

00:39:55.339 --> 00:39:56.172
